news.title: Three of China's biggest banks to provide support for builders
news.para: Bank of Communications Co Ltd (BoCom) said it agreed to provide a 100 billion yuan ($13.98 billion) line of credit to Vanke and a 20 billion yuan line of credit to Midea Real Estate Holding Ltd, two separate statements issued by the bank said on Wednesday.

news.title: Delhi HC seeks ED's stand on Preeti Chandra's bail plea in money-laundering case
news.para: Appearing before the court on behalf of Chandra, lawyer Adit Pujari said the applicant is a fashion designer and philanthropist, who has been in custody since October 4, 2021, and there are no proceeds of crime relatable to her.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Construction cost up by 20% in two years
news.para: A builder Saurabh Mishra said, “There has been 15 to 20% rise in construction cost in the last couple of years. The cost of iron rod (sariya) has gone up from Rs 52 to Rs 83 per kg after the Russia-Ukraine war. The cost of cement has also gone up by 30% than pre-Covid days.

news.title: Parking spaces in 60% of apartments in Bhubaneswar being misused
news.para: On Monday, the BMC came up with a stricture that if parking norms are not followed within a month of issue of the notice, the establishment will be sealed.

news.title: Graft in PMAY exposed at Jhalawar: Probe
news.para: ​The accused employment assistant was produced before an ACB court on Tuesday that ordered to send him to judicial custody.

news.title: Chennai development body demolishes part of building for setback violations
news.para: According to CMDA officials, the action was taken based on the Madras High Court directive. "There was a litigation and directions were given to the CMDA to remove the portions that were in violation," said an official.

news.title: Kirron Kher's demand to regularise units outside 'lal dora' rejected by Chandigarh admin
news.para: Kher demanded a one-time settlement scheme for regularisation, and a halt to the anti-encroachment drive initiated by the UT against such constructions across the city villages.

news.title: Consumer forum directs Tamil Nadu housing board to pay penalty for delay in possession
news.para: Commission president D Gopinath and members V N Parthiban and T Kalaiyarasi directed the board to pay a compensation of 25,000 for deficiency in service and for causing mental agony, pain, and sufferings.

news.title: Nashik civic body adds stricter tree-plantation clause in new real estate policy
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has drafted a new policy for real estate developers undertaking construction activities in the city. The move is aimed at increasing the city’s green cover.

news.title: Developers in Rajasthan demand reduction in labour cess penalty
news.para: As per rule, the project owners are required to pay BOCW cess of 1% for construction of a building costing more than Rs 10 lakh, within one month after completion. If they don’t deposit the amount, they would be liable to pay a cess of 2% per month.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to construct 8.6 lakh new houses under PMAY-Rural
news.para: The Centre has approved Rs 10,000 crore for the construction of houses under the scheme, on the basis of a proposal submitted by the UP Government. The houses are expected to be ready by March 2024.

news.title: No OC issued for your building in Gurugram? Apply online before Dec 31
news.para: According to HSVP, they have found that a considerable number of residential, commercial and institutional properties have been occupied without valid certificates.

news.title: Gurugram: No work at site for 1.5 years, buyers seek Expressway Tower's audit
news.para: The project was launched on seven acres of land in 2017 with a four-year deadline. However, only 60% of the work has been done to date. Currently, no work is going on at the site and most of the homebuyers have paid almost 90% of the flat cost.

news.title: Gurugram: Court denies anticipatory bail to Ardee City's builder in land fraud cases
news.para: Denying the application of Gopal Das Estates & Housing director Shibani Verma Kapur, additional sessions judge Jasbir Singh observed that the charges were serious and taking such offences “lightly” would be an “injustice”.

news.title: SC asks MHADA for status of FIRs on builders, surplus area
news.para: An order by an SC bench of Justices M R Shah and M M Sundresh seeking details of surplus area surrendered by builders and the status of FIRs in 246 projects has put Mhada in a bind.
